SIMPLE: reckless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reckless
<hw>Reck"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>reccele⟦aacute⟧s</ets>,
<ets>r⟦emac⟧cele⟦aacute⟧s</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Inattentive to
duty; careless; neglectful; indifferent.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rashly negligent; utterly careless or
heedless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It made the king as <qex>reckless</qex> as them diligent.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Heedless; careless; mindless; thoughtless;
negligent; indifferent; regardless; unconcerned; inattentive; remiss;
rash.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Reck"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Reck"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reckling</ent>⟦br⟧
